title: Sansom 66ish
description: This is a distance event with a timed cutoff(s) not a timed endurance event. Finish times will be logged DNF unless all laps are completed within the allotted time. Solo (Elite) Century of 6 laps but with a cutoff based on 90 minute laps (must begin 6th lap by 4:30 pm). 6 laps is going to be very tough to complete. You don't have to be Pro or Cat 1 to participate but we may limit this field to experienced single track endurance racers based on the technical difficulty of the course. Solo (Sport) Half Century of 3 laps with no cutoff time. 3 laps in a day will be plenty tough for most mortals. This should be an extremely well rounded field. 2 Person Relay (Men, Women, Co-ed) 6 laps with a cutoff based on 90 minute laps. Relayers must alternate laps so each rider must ride 3 laps for the team to complete the course. No individual rider will be allowed to ride consecutive laps. The relay teams were extremely fun when we did Hell on Wheels at Northshore. I'm really look forward to doing another event with the relays.
course: Is this the toughest endurance mountain bike event in North Texas? Many will attempt it, few will complete it. Time restrictions are tight, margin for error is slim and the course is difficult. Sansom Park is NOT your typical urban mountain bike trail. 1500' of elevation per each 11 mile lap through loose rock climbs and descents and nary a straightaway over 200 feet long. The trail is fun and challenging and we're doing every bit of it!
registration: Online registration only. No on site registration will be available. Field is limited to a maximum of 100 participants. We expect to sell out before the day of event but you never know for sure. Event will be rescheduled if weather creates an issue.
notes: Cutoff time to begin last lap 7.5 hours after start.
directions: Inspiration Point, Marion Sansom Park

title: Funky Town MonsterX
description:
Trinity Trails, Stock Yards, Bridges, Sansom, Gateway and Sundance Square!!! Rain or shine, come one come all!

Is it an urban ride, is it mountain bike ride, is it cyclocross or road?

Yes!!! and no license is needed to enjoy this adventure.

Every bike will be the wrong bike at some point in the mix but every bike will be fun the entire time. This ride is a very unique mix of urban streets, riverside cycling paths, mountain bike trails and more. The route begins and ends in down town Fort Worth/Sundance Square, it then meanders through the Trinity Trails system to Sansom Park and the Sansom Park montain bike trail. From there we take a short urban jaunt to another leg of the Trinity Trails on into the historic Fort Worth Stock Yards. Another urban excursion takes us to our final leg of the Trinity Trails and on into the Gateway Park mountain bike trails. Everyone then follows the Trinity Trails one final time from Gateway Park and back to Sundance Square.

The route is a bit less than 40 miles of streets and Trinity Trails. Mountain bike loops would be additional to that mileage. All sections are optional, this is not a race. For those wondering, this is NOT the Superman.

Stopping and sight seeing is highly encouraged and bonus points will be awarded to the team who can hit the most pubs along the way. We will provide a map in the near future with recommended "check points" included. Let's all get on our bikes and have fun that day.
course: A mix of urban streets, singletrack and recreational trails.
registration: Day of registration $20, cash only.
notes: NA

Trinity Bicycles
343 Throckmorton
Fort Worth, TX

title: Texas State Ultra Road Race
description: The Texas State Ultra Race is the embodiment of Texas States Universities' commitment to quality competitive cycling.
course:
Road Race:The road race is in the scenic black land prairie. The course will be an interesting mix of fast flat sections, exhilarating descents and rambunctious climbs. Our memorable finish will be at the top of a short hill that should be indicative of any racers skill and strength. 

Time Trail: Our time trial will take place in the breath taking Texas Hill Country and has been described as one of the most interesting the SCCCC has ever seen. It will be approximately 3 miles long up a category 4 climb. 

Criterium:The criterium for our event will be on par with any event in Texas. It will be held in the historic down town of San Marcos. Racers will vie for position on completely closed roads among a throng of cheering onlookers. This event will be a defining race for collegiate racing.

title: Midwestern State University Vuelta del Viento
Red River Riot
description:
The Red River Riot is back and better than ever with the focus being the best and most challenging route possible. This is not an official "race" so don't look for prize money, sag support, or even rules. Get your spot early because prices go up as more riders entry. Early bird entries get in for as little as $20. Every 25 riders takes the price up $5 to a maximum of $40 online. Day of registration will be available for $50.

We're going to give you a great route to follow that will cover well over 100 miles of dirt roads in the scenic Red River area of North Texas. Entry fee includes a great staging area, food, classic t-shirt, swag and will provide directions for everyone to find their way from Point A to Point Z. 

The long route will be around 120 miles The short route will be around 60 miles We may offer a mini route of around 30 miles if there is any interest (These routes are greatness) 

The most current information will most likely be on the Spinistry Facebook page or on Spinistry.com. See you there! REMINDER: This is a self supported ride. There WILL NOT be any aid stations or SAG wagons. Do not attempt this ride if you are uncomfortable being 20 miles from civilization with ZERO support.
course: Dirt roads throughout the scenic Red River Valley. Routes include as many hills as possible.
registration: Register online to save dough.
